data.name: label1.Text
data.value:
Among four tabs " Home " tab controls the features of core keylogging.
It Shows :
Shift key status : True = Pressed, False = Not pressed Control key status : True = Pressed, False = Not pressed Alt key status : True = Pressed, False = Not pressed
Command : It shows the current keys pressed. Commands are some text to execute some operation or to guess words.
Key to accept commamd : You can select a key to execute ( run ) the entered command.
Cleat temo data : You can select a key to clear entered command.
Key to guess words : You can select a key to guess word from entered command.
Monitor Keys : True = Monitoring mode is ON, False = Monitoring mode is OFF.
Lock Keyboard : Checked = Keyboard is locked, Unchecked = Keyboard is unlocked.
Show Keys : Checked = Show Pressed Keys in separated window, Unchecked = Don't show keys.
Notify Icon : Checked = Show notify icon in system tray, Unchecked = Don't show notify icon.
Minimal Interface : Click this button to switch into the minimal view of keylogger. It only shows the textbox of bottom right.
Accept Keys : Is shows the selected Key to accept command.
Clear Key : Is shows the selected Key to clear temp data.

data.name: label2.Text
data.value:
Here, Start is active window name where you are typing. For example , if you are typing in Notepad, it will display Notepad instead of Start.
It displays the active windows name. If you are pressing some keys inside some program, it then displays the name of the program.
Shift : When Shift key is pressed down it will display True otherwise False.
Ctrl : When Ctrl key is pressed down it will dispaly True otherwise False.
Alt : When Alt key is pressed down it will display True otherwise False.

data.name: label3.Text
data.value:
This textbox displays the keystrokes and active title.
For Example, Here Keylogger is title of the program where "THIS IS KEYLOGGEROemPerriod STARTNEWPrintScreen" are keys pressed in KeyLogger Program.
OemPeriod is fullstop(.) You dont need to remember that OemPeriod is fullstop.
You can see all keyloggind data in File>Open Key Logs or just pressed Ctrl and O.

data.name: label4.Text
data.value:
Command :
It displays currently pressed keys. If these keys execute system command or open something mentioned in command to open, then after pressing 'key to accept command' or 'key to guess word' it executes the command of this textbox.
Key to accept command :
It allows you to select a key to execute command. For example, In 'System Command' tab if 'hide' is assigned to hide the keylogger and 'show' is assigned to show the keylogger window, then if you type hide and press the 'Key to accept command',(i.e. Space,Esc,Enter,Alt,Shift,Ctrl..any one selected), the keylogger window will be hidden. And then type show and press the 'Key to accept command' to show the keylogger window.
Clear Temp data :
It simply clears the current command data. For example if you are going to type hide and then press ' Key to accept command' to hide the keylogger but you accidently type hidee or hiiidee or something else then press 'Clear temp data' Key.
Key to Guess Words :
Lets take a example,
Go to 'Guess Words' tab and select Add new then a new window appears. Just for an example in Initial textbox type "i" (without " ") and in Final textbox type " am taking an example" then press OK. Now open any program where you can type ( for example Notepad,Internet Browser ( Internet explorer,Goolgle Chrome,Mozilla Firefox) and type "i" (without column) and press 'Guess Words' then " am taking an example" will be written automatically.

data.name: label5.Text
data.value:
Monitor Keys : True = Monitoring mode on, False =Moniroting mode off
You can change monitoring mode through system command "Stop Monitoring".
Lock Keyboard : Checked = Keyboard is locked, Unchecked =Keyboard is unlocked. When keyboard is locked you can't type anything in any program. Just check the Lock Keyboard and type something in any program like Notepad, you can't type anything, uncheck and you can type normally.
You can also lock or unlock keyboard through system command "Lock Keyboard" and "Unlock Keyboard".
Show Keys : Checked = Show typed keys in separate Windows.
Notify Icon : Checked = Displays notify icon in system tray.
Minimal Interface :
It shows the minimal interface of keylogger. Minimal Interface displays only a textbox which shows the current command.
